
# 👶 **Baby Detection, Tracking & Alert System** (YOLOv5 + YouTube Integration)

<p align="center">
  <img src="docs/banner.jpg" alt="Baby Detection Banner" width="700">
</p>

---

## 📌 **Overview**

This project uses **YOLOv5** to **detect, track, and alert** when a baby moves outside a **predefined safety zone**.

**Supports:**

* 🎥 **Real-time webcam monitoring**
* 📂 **Custom/local videos**
* 📺 **YouTube videos**

**Goal** → Build a **smart baby monitoring system** for nurseries, parents, or research purposes.

---

## 🚀 **Features**

* ✅ **Baby Detection** — Custom-trained YOLOv5 model.
* ✅ **Tracking** — Continuous frame-by-frame tracking.
* ✅ **Safety Zone** — Define a safe area to monitor.
* ✅ **Alert System** — Visual alerts when unsafe.
* ✅ **YouTube Integration** — Direct video processing from YouTube.
* ✅ **Google Colab-Friendly** — No need for a local GPU.

---

## 🛠 **Tech Stack**

| Tool/Library | Purpose                   |
| ------------ | ------------------------- |
| **Python 3** | Programming language      |
| **YOLOv5**   | Object detection          |
| **PyTorch**  | Deep learning             |
| **OpenCV**   | Video processing          |
| **yt-dlp**   | YouTube download          |
| **Pygame**   | Sound alerts (local mode) |

---

## 📂 **Dataset**

* **Source:** Custom dataset via [Roboflow](https://roboflow.com)
* **Size:** \~2,000 annotated baby images
* **Format:** YOLO TXT labels
* **Classes:**

```
0 baby
```

**Example Training Images:**

<p align="center">
  <img src="docs/sample_training.jpg" alt="Training Example" width="500">
</p>

---

## ⚙️ **Setup & Usage** (Google Colab)

### **1️⃣ Clone YOLOv5**

```bash
!git clone https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov5
%cd yolov5
!pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### **2️⃣ Download Dataset**

```bash
curl -L "YOUR_ROBOFLOW_DATASET_LINK" > roboflow.zip
unzip roboflow.zip
```

### **3️⃣ Train Model**

```bash
!python train.py --img 640 --batch 16 --epochs 50 --data data.yaml --weights yolov5s.pt
```

### **4️⃣ Download YouTube Video**

```python
from yt_dlp import YoutubeDL

video_url = "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EISMLMybScA&t=4s"
ydl_opts = {
    "format": "best[ext=mp4]",
    "outtmpl": "/content/baby_video.mp4"
}
with YoutubeDL(ydl_opts) as ydl:
    ydl.download([video_url])
```

### **5️⃣ Run Detection + Alert**

```bash
python detect_and_alert.py --weights runs/train/exp/weights/best.pt --source baby_video.mp4
```

---

## 📊 **Detection Box Colors**

| Color           | Meaning                               |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| 🟦 **Blue Box** | Baby inside safety zone               |
| 🟥 **Red Box**  | Baby outside safety zone (**Alert!**) |

